article.headline: Texas State 102, Texas-Permian Basin 92
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Brandon Bush scored 21 points, including 11 free throws, to help lead Texas State to a 102-92 win over Texas-Permian Basin on Wednesday night. Matt Fullenwider came off the bench to add 15 points, including three 3-pointers. Chris Agwumaro had 11 points and Brandon Thomas scored 10 for the Bobcats (4-5). The Falcons (2-5) turned the ball over 21 times, leading to 31 Texas State points. They trailed 49-34 at the half. Mbye Mansour came off the bench to lead the Falcons with 23 points and 13 rebounds. He hit 10-of-15 from the free-throw line. Nedrie Simmons added 18 points, including three 3-pointers. Jerrod Dastrup added 17 points, 12 from 3-point range.
